          {
            "commit": "1fd243c89e3b221d40ce74b8ef47f1bca760c8f9",
            "subject": "LU-1064 mds: journal locking issue was fixed"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-12-01 07:15:34.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-12-01 08:12:14.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-1064 mds: fix mds_lookup lma removal error path",
        "message": "LU-1064 mds: fix mds_lookup lma removal error path\n\nIn commit 1fd243c89e3b221d40ce74b8ef47f1bca760c8f9 if an error is hit\nremoving the \"lma\" xattr from an updated 2.x inode, then the open\ntransaction handle would never be committed, and the MDS would hang.\n\nThis is unlikely to be a problem, as the only errors fsfilt_set_md()\nwill hit that are not programming bugs are due to IO errors from the\nunderlying disk (which is an even bigger problem).\n\nMake sure that the transaction is committed, even after an error.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: If7d19a2337a12efafacd20d5c4e5c00e85300c1e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
